        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 11:14PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 1114 PM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from Myricks Mill to near Cary, and moving northwest at 5
mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Jeffersonville, Marion, Tarversville, District Path, Myricks Mill,
Fitzpatrick, and Ripley.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
